  "original_title": "\u0d9a\u0dc5\u0dd4\u0db6\u0ddd\u0dc0\u0dd2\u0dbd \u0dbb\u0ddd\u0dc4\u0dbd\u0dda \u0db1\u0dcf\u0db3\u0dd4\u0db1\u0db1 \u0dc3\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0dd4 28\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "28 unidentified bodies in Kalubowila Hospital",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "It is reported that twenty-eight unidentified corpses have been kept in the mortuary of the Kalubowila Teaching Hospital for nearly a year, and its daily activities have been severely disrupted.",
        "The mortuary of this hospital has 36 cold rooms, but six of them have not been used for two weeks due to non-repair, so daily services have to be provided from thirty cold rooms.",
        "Information sources say that the body parts sent for medical tests in two other cold storage rooms have to be stored, so there are only 28 cold storage rooms left and unidentified bodies have been stored in them.",
        "It is said that in some cases, two or three unidentified corpses have to be stored in one cold room because the corpses of people dying of covid infection have to be buried at the morgue.",
        "Due to this situation, the dead bodies which are brought to this hospital daily from nearby hospitals for expert forensic reports have to be kept outside the cold rooms until the tests are completed and sometimes if the guardians of the deceased are late in coming from far away, the dead bodies are kept outside. It is also said to be extended.",
        "It is said that the main reason for this is that the post-mortem examination of the unidentified dead bodies brought from the police domains of Wellawatta, Mirihana, Piyandala, Homagama, Kaduwela, Welikada, Kottawa, Mount Talangama, Kohuwala, Dehiwala, Boralasgamuwa, was not completed."
      ],
